messages.content:
Telecom service providers are required to implement several key measures to enhance their cyber security. These include:
(i) Implementing security safeguards, risk management approaches, and conducting relevant training and adopting best practices and technologies to strengthen telecom cyber security;
(ii) Conducting telecommunication network testing, including hardening, vulnerability assessment, and penetration testing;
(iii) Performing risk assessments, identifying potential threats, and preventing security incidents;
(iv) Establishing a rapid action system to respond to security incidents and mitigate their impact;
(v) Conducting forensic analysis of security incidents to derive learnings and enhance telecom cyber security resilience.
Additionally, they must confirm their adoption of such policies to the Central Government, manage and reduce the risks of security incidents, and ensure compliance with government directions and standards. Regular telecom cyber security audits and prompt reporting of incidents to the government are also mandatory, alongside maintaining Security Operations Centres (SOC) to monitor cyber security threats effectively.
